    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES\n\u2013 The No. 13 USC baseball team scored three runs in the bottom of the eighth inning to break a 4-4 tie and take down San Diego State, 7-4, at Dedeaux Field on Tuesday night.\nThe victory moves the Trojans to 20-1 on the season, while the Aztecs fall to 11-10.\nIsaac Cadena\ndrew a bases-loaded walk with two outs to push across the go-ahead run in the eighth and then\nAbbrie Covarrubias\nsingled through the right side to score two more and make it a three-run USC lead. The Trojans drew four walks and a hit-by-pitch in the eighth.\nFive different USC pitchers combined on the mound to hold San Deigo State to four runs on the night, with\nDiego Velazquez\ngetting the win as the pitcher of record in the eighth.\nVelazquez tossed 1.2 scoreless innings of relief, giving up no hits and no walks while striking out three batters. Velazquez entered with runners on second and third and no outs in the seventh, getting a fly out and strikeout to end the inning and hold the Aztecs to just two runs in the frame.\nAfter Velazquez set the side down in order in the eighth and the Trojan bats rallied in the bottom half of the inning,\nAdam Troy\ntossed a scoreless ninth to pick up his seventh save of the season.\nSan Diego State struck first in the game, scoring twice in the top of the first to take an early lead. USC came right back with four runs in the bottom of the first, getting a three-run homer from\nKevin Takeuchi\nand an RBI-double from\nAugie Lopez\n. Takeuchi also worked a walk to lead off the eighth.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nDiego Velazquez\n: W, 1.2 IP, 0H, 0R, 0BB, 3K\nAdam Troy\n: S, 1.0 IP, 0H, 0R, BB\nKevin Takeuchi\n: 2-for-3, 3 RBI, 2R, 3-R HR, BB\nCOMING UP\nUSC hosts CSU Bakersfield on Wednesday and then Big Ten play resumes on Friday as Washington comes to Dedeaux Field for a three-game set. All USC home games will be broadcast on B1G+.\nHear from\n@KevinTakeuchi8\nafter his 3 RBI and 2 runs helped lead to a Trojan W on Tuesday night \u270c\ufe0f\n#FightOn\nx\n@YETICoolers\npic.twitter.com/9mOCBoO3GT\n\u2014 USC Baseball (@USC_Baseball)\nMarch 18, 2026"
  },
